cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with deep learning approaches to aesthetics quality assessment, which involves image analysis and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses pre-trained features and a custom shallow CNN architecture, which are related to machine learning and neural networks, respectively. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, such as feature extraction and pooling, which could make cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a relevant category. Finally, since the paper proposes a new method for aesthetics prediction, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be a possible category.
